article_title: New York City Mayoral Inauguration Is Populist Event
article_text:
Mayor Bill de Blasio's inauguration ceremony was a lively, musical, sometimes funny and starkly populist event that brought together New York's most powerful politicians, a smattering of celebrities and thousands of bundled-up supporters to mark a seismic turn in the city's political universe.

The ceremony, which lasted more than an hour, appeared designed to match Mr. de Blasio's promise to reduce income inequality in the boroughs outside of Manhattan. At times, the event became sharply partisan and somewhat angry. The...

article_summary:
At times, the event became sharply partisan and somewhat angry.
Mayor Bill de Blasio's inauguration ceremony was a lively, musical, sometimes funny and starkly populist event that brought together New York's most powerful politicians, a smattering of celebrities and thousands of bundled-up supporters to mark a seismic turn in the city's political universe.
The ceremony, which lasted more than an hour, appeared designed to match Mr. de Blasio's promise to reduce income inequality in the boroughs outside of Manhattan.
